# firmware signing keys (secp256k1) must NEVER be committed.
# Convention: keep the real release key OUTSIDE the repo (password manager /
# encrypted volume) and pass it via SIGN_KEY=. These patterns are a backstop
# against a stray local copy. See wiznet-io/OTA.md "Release signing & publishing".
*-release.pem
*-signing.pem

# docs.db is a build artifact: CMake builds it from db/docs.sql
# (the committed source-of-truth) and installs it into the .deb.
db/docs.db
